{"type":"message","id":"44ae3d58","parentId":"92fce705","timestamp":"2026-03-20T07:21:23.585Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Friday, March 20th, 2026 — 15:21 (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-03-20 07:21 UTC"}],"timestamp":1773991283584}}
{"type":"message","id":"1ef05815","parentId":"44ae3d58","timestamp":"2026-03-20T07:21:29.601Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"First, the user is starting a new session via /new or /reset. I need to run the Session Startup sequence. According to the instructions, before doing anything else, I must:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who I am\n\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who I'm helping\n\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with my human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nI'm in a direct chat with the user (webchat, direct), so this is a MAIN SESSION. I need to read MEMORY.md as well.\n\nThe current date is Friday, March 20th, 2026. So today's memory file should be `memory/2026-03-20.md` and yesterday's should be `memory/2026-03-19.md`.\n\nI should use the read tool to read these files.\n\nAlso, the user mentioned that the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt. From the system prompt, default_model is \"openrouter/xiaomi/mimo-v2-flash\", and runtime model is also \"openrouter/xiaomi/mimo-v2-flash\" – wait, let me check.\n\nIn the system prompt: \"model=openrouter/xiaomi/mimo-v2-flash | default_model=openrouter/xiaomi/mimo-v2-flash\". They are the same. But the user says \"if the runtime model differs from default_model\". Since they are the same, I shouldn't mention it. But the instruction says \"if the runtime model differs\", so only mention it if it differs. In this case, it doesn't, so I won't mention it.\n\nNow, for the greeting: I need to greet the user in my configured persona. I should read SOUL.md to know my persona. Also, read USER.md to know the user.\n\nAfter reading the files, I should greet in 1-3 sentences, ask what they want to do, and be myself – use my voice, mannerisms, mood.\n\nI must not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\n\nSo, first, I need to read the required files using the read tool.\n\nLet's list the files:\n\n- SOUL.md\n\n- USER.md\n\n- memory/2026-03-20.md\n\n- memory/2026-03-19.md\n\n- MEMORY.md (since it's a main session)\n\nI should read them in order. But I can read multiple files at once since the read tool can be called multiple times.\n\nI'll start with reading SOUL.md, then USER.md, then memory files, and finally MEMORY.md.\n\nAfter reading, I'll greet the user.\n\nAlso, the current time is given, but I don't need to use it unless relevant.\n\nNow, let's execute the read commands.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0f812073603f40c595cd2609","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/zhangyanbo/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-flash","usage":{"input":13415,"output":1286,"cacheRead":110,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14811,"cost":{"input":0.00120735,"output":0.00037294,"cacheRead":0.00000495,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0015852400000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773991283585}}
{"type":"message","id":"ed662b49","parentId":"1ef05815","timestamp":"2026-03-20T07:21:29.617Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0f812073603f40c595cd2609","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773991289613}}
{"type":"message","id":"67dfcfcb","parentId":"ed662b49","timestamp":"2026-03-20T07:21:31.747Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now read USER.md.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f610c22f994e42838d4dcf81","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/zhangyanbo/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-flash","usage":{"input":1048,"output":43,"cacheRead":13524,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14615,"cost":{"input":0.00009432,"output":0.00001247,"cacheRead":0.00060858,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0007153699999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773991289617}}
{"type":"message","id":"f80b7cd8","parentId":"67dfcfcb","timestamp":"2026-03-20T07:21:31.756Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f610c22f994e42838d4dcf81","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md - About Your Human\n\n_Learn about the person you're helping. Update this as you go._\n\n- **Name:**\n- **What to call them:**\n- **Pronouns:** _(optional)_\n- **Timezone:**\n- **Notes:**\n\n## Context\n\n_(What do they care about? What projects are they working on? What annoys them? What makes them laugh? Build this over time.)_\n\n---\n\nThe more you know, the better you can help. But remember — you're learning about a person, not building a dossier. Respect the difference.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773991291752}}
